article.headline: Creighton 69, Indiana State 53
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Anthony Tolliver scored 15 points to lead four Bluejays in double figures as Creighton beat Indiana State 69-53 on Sunday. The Bluejays (11-4, 5-2 Missouri Valley Conference) dominated from the tip-off and led 40-19 at the half on 17-of-26 shooting. For the game, Creighton outshot the Sycamores 52.8 percent to 33.9 percent from the field and outrebounded the host team 36-27. Tolliver, who shot 7-of-9 overall, was followed by Johnny Mathies with 14, Nick Porter with 12 and Dane Watts with 10. Trent Wurtz led Indiana State (8-7, 1-6) with 13 points, including 5-of-6 from the line. Gabriel Moore and Tyson Schnitker each had 10. The Sycamores outscored the Bluejays on turnovers 11-4 and had a 6-5 edge on second-chance points. But Creighton's 28-of-53 shooting outshone Indiana State's 19-of-56 performance and the Bluejays outscored the Sycamores 37-22 in the paint.
